&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enthusiastic, hardworking team member to provide support for midwifery staff in the ward setting, working within the principles of the Trust Values.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To liaise with and report to midwives about women’s and babies conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work under the direction of the midwives to plan, organise and prioritise care for women and their babies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the maintenance and smooth running of the wards/clinics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Taking and recording observations, temperature, pulse, respirations, urine testing and blood pressure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As this is a 24 hour service this position involves working shifts consisting of Long Days and Nights and includes bank holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Appropriate training will be given to link in with the role. Band 2.&lt;/p&gt;
